1. Problem statement
This problem is from Codeforces Div-2 B difficulty. The problem is as follows:
You are given a rectangular array A of N rows and M columns. Each element of the array is either 0 or 1. You can change each 0 to 1, but can at most change K zeros to 1. What is the maximum area (number of 1s) you can make?

2. Input format
The first line contains three integers N, M and K.
The next N lines contain M characters each. Each character is either '0' or '1'.

3. Output format
Print a single integer — the maximum area you can get.

4. Constraints
1≤N,M≤50
0≤K<N⋅M

5. Solution method
The solution method involves using a dynamic programming approach to solve this problem. The algorithm starts by initializing a 2D array dp of size (N+1)×(M+1), where dp[i][j][k] represents the maximum number of 1s that can be made by changing k zeros at most to 1s from the first i rows and j columns of the matrix.

The initial state of the dp array is dp[0][0][0], which is equal to 0. For each 0≤i<N and 0≤j<M, dp[i][j][k] is equal to max(dp[i-1][j][k], dp[i][j-1][k]) if A[i-1][j-1]=1, or max(dp[i-1][j][k], dp[i][j-1][k], dp[i-1][j-1][k-1]+1) if A[i-1][j-1]=0. The algorithm then returns dp[N][M][K].

Below is the C++ code for the solution:



#include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

int dp[51][51][1001];

int main() {
    int N, M, K;
    cin >> N >> M >> K;
    vector<vector<int>> A(N, vector<int>(M));
    for (int i = 0; i < N; i++) {
        for (int j = 0; j < M; j++) {
            cin >> A[i][j];
        }
    }
    dp[0][0][0] = 0;
    for (int i = 1; i <= N; i++) {
        for (int j = 1; j <= M; j++) {
            for (int k = 0; k <= K; k++) {
                dp[i][j][k] = max(dp[i-1][j][k], dp[i][j-1][k]);
                if (A[i-1][j-1] == 0 && k > 0) {
                    dp[i][j][k] = max(dp[i][j][k], dp[i-1][j-1][k-1] + 1);
                }
            }
        }
    }
    cout << dp[N][M][K] << endl;
    return 0;
}


