## Problem Statement

You are given a string s consisting of n lowercase Latin letters.

You can perform the following operation any number of times (possibly zero):

Choose a substring of s that consists of at least two consecutive equal letters.
Remove this substring from s.
For example, if s = "abbab", then the following operations can be performed:

Remove the substring "bb" from s, resulting in s = "aaba".
Remove the substring "aa" from s, resulting in s = "aba".
Remove the substring "ba" from s, resulting in s = "ab".
Remove the substring "ab" from s, resulting in s = "a".
You are given an integer k. You want to perform exactly k operations such that the length of the resulting string is minimized.

Determine the minimum possible length of the resulting string that can be obtained after performing exactly k operations.

Note that the operations are performed in any order.

## Input Format

The first line of the input contains a single integer t (1≤t≤1000) — the number of test cases.

The first line of each test case contains two integers n and k (2≤n≤105, 0≤k≤n) — the length of the string s and the number of operations to perform.

The second line of each test case contains a string s consisting of n lowercase Latin letters.

## Output Format

For each test case, print a single integer — the minimum possible length of the resulting string that can be obtained after performing exactly k operations.

## Constraints

1≤t≤1000
2≤n≤105
0≤k≤n
s consists only of lowercase Latin letters.

## Sample Input 1

```
3
5 1
ababa
5 2
ababa
5 3
ababa
```

## Sample Output 1

```
1
2
3
```

## Explanation

In the first test case, you can perform the following operation:

Remove the substring "ab" from s, resulting in s = "aba".
In the second test case, you can perform the following operations:

Remove the substring "ab" from s, resulting in s = "aba".
Remove the substring "ba" from s, resulting in s = "a".
In the third test case, you can perform the following operations:

Remove the substring "ab" from s, resulting in s = "aba".
Remove the substring "ba" from s, resulting in s = "a".
Remove the substring "a" from s, resulting in s = "".

## Solution

```cpp
#include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

int main() {
    int t;
    cin >> t;
    while (t--) {
        int n, k;
        cin >> n >> k;
        string s;
        cin >> s;
        int ans = n;
        for (char c = 'a'; c <= 'z'; c++) {
            int cnt = 0;
            for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
                if (s[i] == c) {
                    cnt++;
                } else {
                    cnt = 0;
                }
                if (cnt >= 2) {
                    ans = min(ans, n - k);
                }
            }
        }
        cout << ans << endl;
    }
    return 0;
}
```

