## Problem Statement

You are given a string s consisting of n lowercase Latin letters.

A string t is called a substring of s if it can be obtained from s by deletion of several (possibly, zero or all) letters from the beginning and several (possibly, zero or all) letters from the end.

For example, strings "a", "b", "z", "by", "abcz" and "zzaby" are substrings of string s="abczaby", but strings "zzabyy", "zzabyz" and "zzab" are not substrings of s.

Your task is to rearrange the letters in s in such a way that the length of the longest substring that is a palindrome is maximized.

You have to answer t independent test cases.

## Input

The first line of the input contains one integer t (1≤t≤104) — the number of test cases. Then t test cases follow.

The first line of the test case contains one integer n (1≤n≤2⋅105) — the length of the string s.

The second line of the test case contains the string s consisting of n lowercase Latin letters.

It is guaranteed that the sum of n over all test cases does not exceed 2⋅105.

## Output

For each test case, print the answer — the maximum possible length of the longest substring that is a palindrome.

## Example

